{"metadata":{"objective":"","lastStepAudioPath":"summary","audioPath":"QS11/2/Refresher"},"steps":[{"headerText":"","leftText":"<p><span class=\"ju-cktitle\" style=\"color:#025B5B;font-family:lato,sans-serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:bold;\">Fencing shortfall?&nbsp;</span><br /><br />You are the property manager of a resort hotel that is opening in two days, and you are trying to get the pool area ready!<br /><br />Before the pool and hot tub are filled with water, they each must be enclosed by a fence that is 6 feet tall.&nbsp; The fencing material is on site and the contractor is coming to install the fencing today.<br /><br />You just remembered that you ordered fencing before the hotel manager decided to add the hot tub to the pool area.&nbsp; You know that you ordered extra fencing, but you&rsquo;re not sure that you have enough.<br /><br />You look at the order form, which states that you ordered 300 feet of fencing.&nbsp; Now you would like to find out how much fencing you actually need.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"A diagram shows that the pool area consists of a large rectangular patio around the pool and a smaller square patio around the hot tub. The length of this shared portion is the same as the length of one side of the hot tub area, or 22 feet.</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"9"},"leftText":"<p>A&nbsp;<strong>math expression</strong>&nbsp;is made up of numbers and operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, or division.&nbsp; A <strong>formula</strong> shows how the numbers are related.<br /><br />Write a math expression using the perimeter of a rectangle formula to find the perimeter of the pool area and substitute the values you know for L and W.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>P = 2L + 2W,&nbsp; where L = 80 and W = 50</p><p>P = 2<span class=\"screen-reader-only\" style=\"background-color:#FA839F;\"> times </span>(80) + 2<span class=\"screen-reader-only\" style=\"background-color:#FA839F;\"> times </span>(50)</p><p>P = 160 + 100</p><p>P = 260<br /><br />The perimeter of the pool area rectangle is 260 feet.</p>","headerText":"Next, write a math expression and do the math."},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"10"},"leftText":"<p>Write a math expression using the perimeter of a square formula to find the perimeter of the hot tub area and substitute the value you know for S.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>P = 4<span class=\"screen-reader-only\" style=\"background-color:#FA839F;\">&nbsp;</span>S, where S = 22</p><p>P = 4<span class=\"screen-reader-only\" style=\"background-color:#FA839F;\"> times </span>(22)</p><p>P = 88<br /><br />The perimeter of the hot tub area square is 88 feet.</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"11"},"leftText":"<p>Find the total perimeter of both areas.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>Total perimeter&nbsp; = pool perimeter + hot tub perimeter</p><p>Total perimeter&nbsp; = 260 + 88</p><p>Total perimeter&nbsp; = 348</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The total perimeter of the pool and hot tub areas is 348 feet.</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"12"},"leftText":"<p>Subtract the length of the section of fencing that is shared.<br /><br />This is the same as the length of one side of the hot tub, or 22 feet.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"A diagram shows the pool and hot tub areas.  One side of the hot tub area, which is 22 feet long, is shared with part of the long side of the pool area.   The 22 foot side that is shared with the pool area is the length of the shared fencing that needs to be subtracted.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>`348 - 22 = 326`</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"13"},"leftText":"<p>You need 326 feet of fencing to enclose both the pool area and the hot tub area!<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":null},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"14"},"leftText":"<p>Ask yourself: &nbsp;<strong>Does my answer make sense?</strong><br /><br />Try one of these ways to &quot;quick check&quot; your answer without doing all of the calculations again:</p><ul><li>Think about the situation and numbers involved.&nbsp; Use logic to decide if your answer seems reasonable.</li><li>Do a simpler version of the calculation.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"For example, if you are calculating the height of a human and your answer is 14 feet, your answer is not reasonable. 14 feet would be a reasonable answer if you were calculating the height of a yeti.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p>","headerText":"Finally, make sure your answer makes sense, and state it clearly"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"15"},"leftText":"<p>Check by adding the lengths of all of the sides that need fencing.<br /><br />This confirms that your answer makes sense!<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p><img alt=\"A diagram shows the pool and hot tub areas with all of the lengths that need to be added together to get the total perimeter.   The short side of the pool area is 50 feet long.    The long side of the pool area that is shared with the hot tub area is 80 minus 22 feet = 58 feet long.   The four sides of the hot tub area are each 22 feet long.  The other short side of the pool area is 50 feet long, and the final long side off the pool area is 80 feet long.\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p><p>50 + 58 + 22 + 22 +22 + 22 + 50 + 80 = 326</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"16"},"leftText":"<p>Will your original order of 300 feet of fencing be enough?<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>You need 326 feet of fencing.</p><p>You originally ordered 300 feet</p><p>`326 - 300 = 26`</p><p>You need 26 feet more of fencing to enclose both the pool and the hot tub areas.</p>","headerText":"Do you need to order more fencing?"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"fullWhiteboard":0,"audioPath":"17"},"leftText":"<p>Because of the addition of the hot tub, the amount of fencing you ordered is not enough.<br /><br />You need to order more fencing right away, then let the contractor know that the fencing installation job is delayed until tomorrow!<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":null,"headerText":""}],"overviewHeader":"Overview"}
